re, Scotland":"Kyle of Lochalsh, Ross-shire, Schotland"},"en":{"Abt 1452–":"about 1452–Deceased","1448–1494":"1448–1494","1470–1519":"1470–1519","1475–Male":"1475–Deceased","1477–Male":"1477–Deceased","1480–Male":"1480–Deceased","1482–Male":"1482–Deceased","1490–1525":"1490–1525","1492–Female":"1492–Deceased","1452–Female":"1452–Deceased","about 1480":"about 1480","about 1470":"about 1470","about 1490":"about 1490","1494":"1494","1482":"1482","1492":"1492","1470":"1470","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1525":"1525","1448":"1448","1477":"1477","Abt 1452":"about 1452","1475":"1475","1452":"1452","about 1477":"about 1477","about 1475":"about 1475","1519":"1519","about 1482":"about 1482","Co Heretrix / Kyle of Lochalsh, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kyle of Lochalsh, Ross-shire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland, United Kingdom","Kyle of Lochalsh, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kyle of Lochalsh, Ross-shire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"MacDonald","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish:  see  McDonald  ."],"variants":[{"name":"McDonald","meanings":["Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <i>Mac Domhnaill</i> ‘son of <i>Domhnall</i>’, a name derived from the Celtic elements <i>domno-</i> ‘world’ + <i>val-</i> ‘might, rule’. <i>Donald</i> is an Anglicized form (via Latin) of this personal name used in Scotland, though the surname is also widespread in Ireland. The name is equivalent to Irish   McDonnell   and   McConnell  , and to Manx   Cannell  .","History: This is the name of the largest and most disparate of the Scottish clans (Clan Donald), associated in particular with the Hebrides and claiming descent from Domhnall mac Raghnaill mac Somhairle, who lived in the late 12th century. From that time until 1493 the head of the clan was known as Lord (or King) of the Isles. The reigns of the Lords of the Isles were always stormy, often in conflict with the kings of Scotland, and peppered with disasters. After a series of defeats in the 1480s, Eoin Mac Dhomhnaill a Ìle (John Macdonald of Islay, Earl of Ross and Lord of the Isles) forfeited his lands, his power, and his title as Lord of the Isles in 1493 to King James IV of Scotland. By then, a branch of the family had settled in the Antrim Glens in Ireland and members moved between the southern Hebrides and Ireland throughout the 16th century."]}]},{"name":"Ingen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Ingegerd   and   Ingrid  , attested from the 16th-century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Ingen MacDonald Of Localsh was born about 1452, in Scotland, United Kingdom. She had at least 5 sons and 2 daughters with Sir Alexander MacDonald 2nd of Lochalsh."},"et":{"Abt 1452–":"umbes 1452–Surnud","1448–1494":"1448–1494","1470–1519":"1470–1519","1475–Male":"1475–Surnud","1477–Male":"1477–Surnud","1480–Male":"1480–Surnud","1482–Male":"1482–Surnud","1490–1525":"1490–1525","1492–Female":"1492–Surnud","1452–Female":"1452–Surnud","about 1480":"umbes 1480","about 1470":"umbes 1470","about 1490":"umbes 1490","1494":"1494","1482":"1482","1492":"1492","1470":"1470","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1525":"1525","1448":"1448","1477":"1477","Abt 1452":"umbes 1452","1475":"1475","1452":"1452","about 1477":"umbes 1477","about 1475":"umbes 1475","1519":"1519","about 1482":"umbes 1482","Co Heretrix / Kyle of Lochalsh, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kyle of Lochalsh, Ross-shire, Scotland","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Kyle of Lochalsh, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kyle of Lochalsh, Ross-shire, Scotland"},"fi":{"Abt 1452–":"noin 1452–Kuollut","1448–1494":"1448–1494","1470–1519":"1470–1519","1475–Male":"1475–Kuollut","1477–Male":"1477–Kuollut","1480–Male":"1480–Kuollut","1482–Male":"1482–Kuollut","1490–1525":"1490–1525","1492–Female":"1492–Kuollut","1452–Female":"1452–Kuollut","about 1480":"noin 1480","about 1470":"noin 1470","about 1490":"noin 1490","1494":"1494","148